== Preface ==

The goal of this action is to make politicians aware that the "compromise" reached at the Council session of 18 May is bogus for many reasons. Since they may receive many times the same letter, '''make sure you add a personal message of at least half a page or so''', preferably with your company logo on it.

'''When you have sent a letter, had telephonic contact, ..., please note this on the''' [:LtrConsSendBe0406En: follow-up page].

If you have any suggestions for content to be added to this page, please contact jmaebe AT ffii.org

== Letters and annexes ==

=== Letters ===

==== Minimal letter ====

This version does not contain any references to appendixes. Useful for quick sending to raise awareness, and as accompanying document with a personal or company letter.

[http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsMinim0406.nl.pdf Dutch] ([http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsMinim0406.nl.sxw OpenOffice version]) | [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsMinim0406.fr.pdf French] ([http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsMinim0406.fr.sxw OpenOffice version])

==== Full pre-addressed letters ====

This version contains references to the appendixes below and is intended to be sent together with them, although you can edit the provided !OpenOffice document to remove them if you don't feel like sending all of them.

 * Federal
   * Premier Verhofstadt: [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsVerhofstadt0406.nl.pdf Dutch PDF] | [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsVerhofstadt0406.fr.pdf French PDF]
   * Minister Verwilghen: [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsVerwilghen0406.nl.pdf Dutch PDF] | [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsVerwilghen0406.fr.pdf French PDF]
 * Wallonia:
   * Minister Marcourt: [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsMarcourt0406.fr.pdf French PDF] | [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsMarcourt0406.fr.sxw French Open Office document] (usable to create letters to other French speaking politicians)
 * Flanders:
   * Minister Moerman: [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsMoerman0406.nl.pdf Dutch PDF] | [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/appeal0406/LtrConsMoerman0406.nl.sxw Dutch Open Office document] (usable to create letters to other Dutch speaking politicians)
